{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048182,"nonce":"25LL/g7K12NLYSlpi8pledjyLhs=","title":"Configurable body parameterization (N-DOF chains, variable morphology)","message":"[Imported from GitHub #51] (created 2026-02-21T23:27:45Z)\n\n## Motivation\n\nCurrent plants (TwoLinkArm, PointMass, MuscledArm) have hardcoded topologies and parameters. TwoLinkArm is fixed at 2 DOF with 6 muscles; MuscledArm bakes moment arms into `__init__`. This limits feedbax to a narrow set of body configurations.\n\nA configurable body parameterization would let feedbax:\n- Train controllers on arbitrary N-DOF serial chains\n- Generalize across body types (varying segment lengths, masses, muscle properties)\n- Condition neural controllers on body parameters (φ) for universal policies\n\n## Proposed Design\n\nA `BodyPreset` dataclass (adapted from bbooddyy) specifying:\n- Segment lengths, masses, inertias\n- Joint damping, stiffness\n- Muscle PCSA, optimal fiber length, tendon slack length, activation time constants\n- `to_flat()` / `from_flat()` for neural conditioning vectors\n- `BodyPresetBounds` for random sampling across morphologies\n\nThis feeds into skeleton/plant constructors: `BodyPreset → MuJoCo MJCF XML → MjModel → MJXPlant` (for MJX) or `BodyPreset → skeleton parameters` (for analytical models).\n\n## Scope\n\n- Configurable N-DOF planar chains (immediate)\n- 3D articulated bodies (future)\n- Integration with MJXPlant (planned) and existing analytical skeletons\n- Body-conditioned controllers via φ embedding\n\n## Relation to Other Work\n\n- bbooddyy issue #1: migrating BodyPreset from bbooddyy to feedbax\n- feedbax #50: alternative training methods (body-conditioned RL)\n- feedbax #33: improve musculoskeletal geometry realism\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}